BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
PRODID:-//Chad Kuehn//Catholic Calendar//EN
X-WR-CALNAME:Catholic
X-WR-TIMEZONE:America/Chicago

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ashwednesday-2026@customcalendar
SUMMARY:Ash Wednesday
DESCRIPTION:Ash Wednesday marks the beginning of Lent\, the 40-day penitential season before Easter. Catholics and many other Christians receive ashes in the sign of the cross on their foreheads as a sign of mortality\, humility\, and repentance\, recalling: Remember that you are dust\, and to dust you shall return.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260218
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260219
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:allsaints-2026@customcalendar
SUMMARY:All Saints' Day
DESCRIPTION:A holy day of obligation in the Catholic Church observed on November 1\, honoring all the saints — both known and unknown — who have attained heaven. The faithful are called to attend Mass and to pray for the intercession of the saints.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261102
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:allsouls-2026@customcalendar
SUMMARY:All Souls' Day
DESCRIPTION:Observed on November 2\, All Souls' Day is a day of prayer and remembrance for the faithful departed — those believed to be in purgatory awaiting full entry into heaven. Catholics offer prayers\, Masses\, and acts of charity for the souls of the deceased.
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261102
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261103
END:VEVENT

